article.headline: IPFW 65, SE Missouri State 64
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- DeWitt Scott scored 24 points for Indiana Purdue-Fort Wayne as the Mastodons beat Southeast Missouri State 65-64 Monday night. IPFW (1-1) started the game with 13 unanswered points before Southeast Missouri finally scored nearly five minutes into the game. The Mastadons led by as many as 14 points in the first half before going in with a 38-25 lead at the break. The Redhawks (1-1) also started slowly in the second half, going down by 17 when IPFW's Tyler Best hit a layup to make the score 44-27 with 17:53 remaining. But Southeast Missouri went on an 11-0 run to get back into the game, and eventually pulled to within four with 2:35 left. The Redhawks got to within one on Roy Booker's 3-pointer with 23 seconds remaining, but Scott hit a pair of free throws with 4 seconds left to put IPFW back up by three. Southeast Missouri made a tip-in shot at the buzzer for the final tally. Quintin Carouthers scored 14 and Justin Hawkins added 10 for the Mastadons. Booker led Southeast Missouri with 25 points, while Ketschner Guerrier had 11 points and 11 rebounds for the Redhawks.
